headline: NetApp Insider Sales Pattern Emerges As Shares Screen As Undervalued
summary: On February 10, 2026, NetApp (NasdaqGS:NTAP) Executive Vice President and Chief Administrative Officer Elizabeth O'callahan sold additional company shares. This transaction adds to a broader pattern of insider sales at NetApp over the past year. The activity is drawing attention from investors who monitor insider trades as one input for assessing management sentiment. NetApp, a data management and storage company, operates in a sector that continues to adjust to growing cloud adoption,...
